      "date": "2011-08-02 22:01:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(11 inline comments)\n\nSorry for the confusion here.  This patch is now the mashup of the first approach (using errno to pass the status to llapi_err()) which was very messy and hard to maintain, and the second approach (using \"rc\" from llapi_*() functions and passing this directly to llapi_error()).\n\nPlease remove the changes that were setting \"errno\" before returning this same value as \"rc\", and just use \"rc\" to pass to llapi_error().  I've pointed out some of the places in the liblustreapi.c patch that should be changed, but there are many more.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "bc836a9a40f0218ba82cade2d3cab0930e890504",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-08-02 22:19:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: (1 inline comment)\n\nPlease ignore comment about using llapi_printf() instead of llapi_err_noerrno().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "f7d94bda84a5ad98634c43657999fea3ae230894",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 103,
        "name": "Zhenyu Xu",
        "email": "bobijam@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bobijam"
      },
      "date": "2011-08-03 03:42:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nSo I'd put llapi_xxx() returns negative value upon failure, quit messing up with errno at least in our libraries.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
